This is what he said:\q1 "I hear people screaming because they are terrified;
\q2 there is no peace in the land.


\q1

9:
My people will again serve me, Yahweh, their God,\q2 and they will serve a king who is a descendant of King David;
\q2 and I will appoint this king for them.


\q1

12:
Yahweh also says this:\q1 "You have suffered very much;
\q2 it is as though you have a terrible wound that cannot be cured.
\q1

19:
People will again sing joyfully to thank me,\q2 and I will cause there to be more people in Jerusalem, not fewer;
\q2 I will cause them to be honored, not despised.


\q1

23:
Yahweh will punish your enemies;\q2 it will be like a great storm;
\q2 it will come down like a whirlwind, swirling around the heads of wicked people.
